<h2>Mores Creek Ambulance Radio Operations</h2>
<h3>General Info</h3>

<p>
	Radio traffic should be kept brief and clear. The use of "codes" and other shortcuts that may 
	cause confusion should be avoided whenever possible. Before keying the microphone, listen to 
	make certain nobody else is using the frequency. After keying the microphone, wait about 
	one second before speaking. This gives all the downstream repeaters and receivers the time to 
	"listen".
</p>

<p>
	All of our radios have a scan mode that allows them to monitor more than one frequency. Once 
	you arrive on-scene, you may elect to turn scan mode off if monitoring Boise county is not 
	necessary.
</p>

