<p>
	StateComm 1 is used to give patient reports to St. Al's and St. Lukes. Both hospitals monitor this frequency. 
	StateComm 2 is our primary frequency, and goes directly to State Comm. Someone on the crew should always be 
	monitoring StateComm 2. When monitoring Boise county dispatch, you can monitor any of the 4 (Hawley, Pilot, 
	Shaw, car/car) frequencies, since they are all the same <em>receive</em> frequency. If you need to talk to Boise 
	county, your best choice will normally be Shaw, which is located west of Hilltop. Pilot, located north of 
	Idaho City, would be a good backup. Hawley is near Banks, and is usually a poor choice for us. Car/car, BCF1, 
	and BCF2 do not use repeaters. These frequencies are good for short range only.
</p>

